label_set = set(mushroom_dataset['label'])
for label in label_set:
    print(label)

For iris dataset¶

average, standard deviation, and value frequency¶

In [13]:
iris_class_set = set(iris_dataset['iris_class'])
for iris_class in iris_class_set:
    print(iris_class)
    iris_dataset_temp = iris_dataset[iris_dataset['iris_class'] == iris_class]
    iris_mean = iris_dataset_temp.mean()
    print(iris_mean)
    iris_mean.plot.bar(title='The average of iris')
    iris_std = iris_dataset_temp.std()
    print(iris_std)
    iris_std.plot.bar(title='The standard deviation of iris')
    for i in iris_dataset_temp.columns:
        print(f'{i}\n{iris_dataset_temp[i].value_counts()}\n')
        iris_dataset_temp[i].value_counts().sort_index().plot.bar(title=f'Freq dist of {i}')
        plt.show()

In [16]:
# mashroom
mushroom_dataset_shuffle = shuffle(mushroom_dataset)
mushroom_x = (mushroom_dataset_shuffle.drop(mushroom_dataset_shuffle.columns[0], axis=1))
mushroom_y = np.array(mushroom_dataset_shuffle[mushroom_dataset_shuffle.columns[0]])
le_mushroom = preprocessing.LabelEncoder()
mushroom_x_le = np.array(mushroom_x.apply(le_mushroom.fit_transform))
le_mushroom.fit(mushroom_y)
mushroom_y_le = le_mushroom.transform(mushroom_y)
# iris
iris_dataset_shuffle = shuffle(iris_dataset)
iris_x = np.array(iris_dataset_shuffle.drop(iris_dataset_shuffle.columns[-1], axis=1))
iris_y = np.array(iris_dataset_shuffle[iris_dataset_shuffle.columns[-1]])
le_iris = preprocessing.LabelEncoder()
le_iris.fit(iris_y)
iris_y_le = le_iris.transform(iris_y)

    mushroom_y_train_K.append(mushroom_y_le[train_index])

In [25]:
def Classification_Accuracy(tp, tn, fp, fn):
    return (tp + tn) / (tp + tn + fp + fn)

def Sensitivity_Recall(tp, fn):
    return tp / (tp + fn)

def Precision(tp, fp):
    return tp / (tp + fp)

def get_tp_tn_fp_fn(confusion_matric):
    print(confusion_matric.ravel())
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matric.ravel()
    return tp, tn, fp, fn

    confusion_matrix_mushroom_K_no_LS += confusion_matrix(mushroom_y_test_K[i], mushroom_y_pred_K_no_LS[i])
    accuracy_score_mushroom_K_no_LS += accuracy_score(mushroom_y_test_K[i], mushroom_y_pred_K_no_LS[i])
    recall_score_mushroom_K_no_LS += recall_score(mushroom_y_test_K[i], mushroom_y_pred_K_no_LS[i], average = None)
    precision_score_mushroom_K_no_LS += precision_score(mushroom_y_test_K[i], mushroom_y_pred_K_no_LS[i], average = None)
confusion_matrix_mushroom_K_no_LS /= n_split
accuracy_score_mushroom_K_no_LS /= n_split
recall_score_mushroom_K_no_LS /= n_split
precision_score_mushroom_K_no_LS /= n_split

Comparison & Conclusion¶

  • accuracy通常是K-fold會比Holdout Validation較好一點
  • 有沒有Laplace smoothing的結果差不多，可能是因為k太小(k為1)

For the mushroom dataset¶

Show P(Xstalk−color−below−ring|Y=e) by histograms¶

In [34]:
stalk_color_below_ring_list = list(set(mushroom_dataset['stalk-color-below-ring']))
stalk_color_below_ring_list.sort()
stalk_color_below_ring_value_count_no_LS = []
stalk_color_below_ring_value_count_with_LS = []
label_e_idx = mushroom_dataset.index[mushroom_dataset['label'] == 'e'].tolist()
# get frequancy and probability
for stalk_color_below_ring in stalk_color_below_ring_list:
    stalk_color_below_ring_value_count_no_LS.append(len(set(label_e_idx) & set(mushroom_dataset.index[mushroom_dataset['stalk-color-below-ring'] == stalk_color_below_ring])) / len(label_e_idx))
    stalk_color_below_ring_value_count_with_LS.append((len(set(label_e_idx) & set(mushroom_dataset.index[mushroom_dataset['stalk-color-below-ring'] == stalk_color_below_ring])) + 1) / (len(label_e_idx) + 1 * len(stalk_color_below_ring_list)))
# plot
plt.title("without Laplace smoothing")
plt.xlabel('stalk-color-below-ring')
plt.ylabel('probability')
plt.bar(stalk_color_below_ring_list, stalk_color_below_ring_value_count_no_LS)
plt.show()
plt.title("with Laplace smoothing, k = 1")
plt.xlabel('stalk-color-below-ring')
plt.ylabel('probability')
plt.bar(stalk_color_below_ring_list, stalk_color_below_ring_value_count_with_LS)
plt.show()

Use a graph to show the probability density function of assumed P(Xpetal_length|Y=Iris-Versicolor)¶

In [36]:
# get data without the condition
petal_length_list = list(set(iris_dataset['petal_length']))
petal_length_list.sort()
petal_length_list_value_count = []
iris_class_versicolor_idx = iris_dataset.index[iris_dataset['iris_class'] == 'Iris-versicolor'].tolist()
# get frequancy and probability
for petal_length in petal_length_list:
    petal_length_list_value_count.append(len(set(iris_class_versicolor_idx) & set(iris_dataset.index[iris_dataset['petal_length'] == petal_length])) / len(iris_class_versicolor_idx))
petal_length_list_with_cond = []
petal_length_list_value_count_with_cond = []
# consider the condition
for i in range(len(petal_length_list)):
    if petal_length_list_value_count[i] > 0:
        petal_length_list_with_cond.append(petal_length_list[i])
        petal_length_list_value_count_with_cond.append(petal_length_list_value_count[i])
# plot
plt.title("probability density function of assumed P(Xpetal_length|Y=Iris-Versicolor)")
plt.xlabel('petal length')
plt.ylabel('probability')
plt.plot(petal_length_list_with_cond, petal_length_list_value_count_with_cond)
plt.show()
